# Ingestion source standards

## Structure of every source file
Each source file must follow this exact pattern:

1. Module docstring explaining what data this source provides
2. Config loaded from environment via dotenv
3. A single main fetch function with typed return (returns pandas DataFrame)
4. A write_to_blob() function that writes Parquet to Azure Blob Storage
5. A if __name__ == "__main__" block that runs fetch + write for local testing

## Azure Blob naming convention
Container: finpulse-bronze
Path pattern: {source_name}/{YYYY-MM-DD}/{source_name}_raw.parquet

## Never do this in ingestion files
- No transformation or cleaning logic (that belongs in Silver notebooks)
- No ML or sentiment scoring (that belongs in Gold)
- No hardcoded tickers or date ranges — always parameterise
